# Interconnections of neurons the reflex


**Important concepts and terms:**
- Name the elements of the spinal chord.
- Elucidate the connection of neurons with the help of the reflex.


**The spinal spinal chord:** 
- ![spinal chord.jpeg](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

**Reflex:**
 A reflex action is an automatic (involuntary) and rapid response to a stimulus, meant to minimises any damage to the body.

**The knee-jerk reflex:**
- The brain is not involved in the knee-jerk reflex. The reaction pathway only leads through the spinal cord why this reflex cannot be influenced voluntarily.
	- Reflex reaction pathway:
	  ![Capture21.png](data:image/png;base64,)
- Contracting and relaxing muscles:
  ![Capture22.png](data:image/png;base64,)

- **The reaction:**
	- The reflex begins when a painful stimulus is detected by a receptor. The activation of this recptor leads to an action potential in a sensory neuron which carries the signal to the spinal cord. 
	- There multiple reflex pathways are activated. 
		- One of those pathways exictes the motor neuron that activated the flexor muscle to withdraw the limb from the  painful stimulus. 
		- Another pathway inhibits the motor neuron that normally activates the oposing extensor muscle in the limb. (This keeps the extensor muscle from counteracting the attempt of the flexor muscle to pull the limb away.)
		- Another pathway crosses over to the other side of the spinal cord and causes the opposite response to occour in the opposing limb. (The extensor muscle in the other limb will be activated and the flexor muscle will be inhibited), (This is enacted for postural support).
